Absolutely positively the best Dominican food next to the Bronx New York......might even be better than Caridad. If you like authentic Dominican fare it's THE place for you. Can you go in jeans & sneakers? Of course but it's even better if you go with someone who speaks fluent Spanish. Very nice owners who aim to please. You must stop there if you are anywhere near Springfield, Mass.

Stopped for a late lunch on 2/21/14 and got a great meal. You can order off the menu or grill or place your order with already prepared food. We chose to order from the prepared food and was not disappointed. Yellow rice and pork chops for me and white rice, beans, soup, and chicken for the rest of the group. We also indulged in the chocoflan and loved it. Can soda for everyone. The servings were huge and the staff were very helpful and polite. I would definitely come here again. Cash or credit no problem. Good parking also.

Best Dominican restaurant in Springfield. There aren't many out here but this one is the best! I come from lawrence where everything is Dominican and this is close to as good as the food there. They are all so friendly too!The menu is extensive and I have yet to find a dish I didn't like.  My favorite dish is "Mofongo con Camarones al Ajillo" (Fried plantain ball with shrimp in garlic sauce).  It is made to order so I have to wait a good 15-20 minutes unless I call ahead but it is so worth it!!  Oh, did I mention take out is available!!
They have the BEST mangoo(hope i spelled right) and have a wide variety of different foods available like liver. They can also make you a burger and fries if that what your in the mood for.
